                    <h3 style="font-size:16px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h3><br />
                    <h3 style="font-size:15px;"><u><b>Shopping </b></u></h3><br />
                    <p>
                        <b>Shopping with Image Solutions </b><br>
                        These pages are designed to answer the most frequently asked questions about your online shopping experience. Shopping online with Image Solutions is easy and fun. As you browse through our site, you may add items to your shopping cart along the way by clicking the "Add to Cart" button found below the items that you choose.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Offerings</b><br>
                        As we transition from HPI to Image Solutions, you will see old and new inventory options available to order.  Once the HPI items have been depleted, they will be removed from the site. <br />
                    </p>
                    <p><b>Personal Information </b><br>
                        You are our first priority. We make every possible effort to respect and protect your privacy. We believe in keeping personal information confidential.<br>
                        <br>
                        To purchase products, you will need to provide certain personal information. You are only asked to provide personal information that is essential to completing your order. Image Solutions uses your information to make your shopping experience as enjoyable as possible.<br> 
                    </p>
                    <p><b>Privacy Tips </b><br>
                        Your account information is password protected and accessible only to you. To safeguard your account, it is recommended that you not share your password with others.<br />
                        No one from Image Solutions will call or e-mail you about your personal account information. If you contact us and request our assistance, then we must verify personal data for security reasons. We advise you to be wary of unsolicited contacts and suggest that you do not reveal your password to anyone.<br />
                        To further protect the integrity of your personal information, close your browser when you step away from your computer, particularly if you are in a public forum.<br />
                    </p>
                    <p><b>Checking Out &nbsp;</b><br>
                        When you have finished shopping and are ready to check out, click on the "Proceed to Checkout" button at the bottom of your shopping cart. Your User Name and Password are recognized and automatically provide you with the opportunity to review all your billing and shipping information.<br />
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>How do I place an order? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        1. Place products in your shopping cart by selecting the number of items and the appropriate size and then click on "Add to Cart". <br>
                        2. When you have picked all your items and you're ready to purchase, click "Proceed to Checkout". <br>
                        3. Payments can only be made with a credit card.<br>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>What if I change my mind about items in my shopping cart prior to placing my order? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        You may update your order by adjusting the quantity of any of the items in your cart. You may also remove items from your cart by clicking on the “View Cart” button and then clicking on “Remove” next to the item you would like to remove.<br />
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>How do I know what my shopping cart total is? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        The subtotal is always displayed with your shopping cart. All appropriate taxes are calculated at the time of invoice. &nbsp;<br />
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Once I start shopping, must I continue to check out? </b><br>
                        No. Your selected merchandise will remain in your shopping cart until such time that you either Check Out on the site, completely log out of your system or delete your cookies. &nbsp;<br />
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Once I've placed an order, can I cancel it? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        As long as the order is still pending or on backorder, it may be cancelled. Please contact our Customer Support Team via email  &nbsp;<br>
                        M-F 8am – 8pm EST <a href="mailto:cs@imageinc.com" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">cs@imageinc.com</a> and available by phone M-F 11am-6pm EST (888)756-9898. &nbsp;<br />
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <br />
                    <h3 style="font-size:15px; "><u><b>General Uniform Program Information</b></u></h3>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>We have an employee that cannot wear wool or polyester, is there an alternative option? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Yes, IMAGE SOLUTIONS can offer a cotton pant. Contact customer service via phone or E-Mail &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>What accommodations can be made for an employee when their size is not on the website? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Image Solutions will check their inventory and make every effort to accommodate the requested size within the uniform program. &nbsp;<br>
                        Here are a couple of options*:<br />
                        1. If you cannot find a small enough size, you can order the closest size available and have the employee alter the clothing and reimburse the employee for the alteration expense.<br />
                        2. If Image Solutions does not offer a large enough size, the employee may purchase their own shirt or pant, providing the clothing is as similar as possible to the uniform program. We will reimburse the employee for this expense. *Please obtain Manager approval. &nbsp;
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Do name tags have to have last names? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        No, name tags require your first name only. &nbsp;
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Can Greeters wear the winter parka or snow suit? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        If it’s below freezing temperatures, it’s understandable if they need to wear the snowsuit. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Who is required to wear uniforms for the Enterprise brand? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        The Enterprise Bus Driver/Shuttle Driver, Service Agents or Sr. Car are part of the uniform program. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>How do I wash and care for my uniform? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        <b>Custom Tailored Dress Pants, Dress, Skirts, Blazers, Blouse, Work Pants and Shorts &nbsp;</b><br>
                        What can I do to keep my uniform looking good and last long? &nbsp;<br>
                        Following proper washing procedures the most important thing. Please refer to the label inside. It is recommended that all tailored items be professionally dry cleaned to keep them in good condition however, you may hand wash, spot treat or machine wash in cold water on a gentle cycle. Please do not use chlorine bleach as it will fade fabrics. Please remove promptly and hang to dry. For Pants &amp; Shorts, turn inside out to wash and dry to protect. Wash in warm or cold water with like colors, tumble dry low and remove promptly. Use warm iron if needed. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        <b>Quick Tip:&nbsp;</b> Professionally dry clean all garments that are marked Dry Clean Only. Polyester/wool fabric will shrink in warm water or warm dryer heat. &nbsp;<br>
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Pants, Polo and Twill Shirts &nbsp;</b><br /><br />
                        If there is a stain on my uniform that regular washing can’t get out, what do I do? &nbsp;<br>
                        First, do not use bleach. Try pre-soaking the shirts to help loosen grease or stains using a spray and wash stain remover such as Shout or Resolve. Always follow the product directions on how to remove the stain on different fabrics. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        <b>My shirts are fraying or pilling, what do I do? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        This can happen when shirts and tailored pants are washed with jackets, jeans, or clothing articles with metals attached, i.e. buttons or zippers. Wash shirts and tailored pants with metal-free clothing. Also, wash on the gentle cycle as normal or heavy cycles may be rough on clothes. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        <b>Our shirts and pants seem to wear out fast. What can I do to prolong them? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Following proper washing procedures is very important. Please refer to the garment label for care instructions. Most garments cab be washed on gentle in cold water with like colors. Tumble dry on the lowest temperature setting. Another option, especially for pants is after washing, immediately remove and hang them out to dry. Ignore the dryer, but be sure to iron. Wearing a white undershirt will prolong the life of your shirts as perspiration is toxic and can degrade the quality of fabric. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        <b>Quick Tip:&nbsp;</b>Use color safe (not chlorine) bleach on dress shirts and pants. Using chlorine on fabrics with polyester can cause the fabric to turn yellow. Performance fabrics or moisture-wicking shirts can snag easily in the washer and dryer. Use a delicate cycle and avoid washing with items that have metal components (like zippers, etc.) Use low heat to dry or lay flat to dry. These light weight fabrics dry quickly. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Sweater &nbsp;</b><br /><br />
                        <b>What can I do to help my Sweater, Soft Shell Vest/Jacket last longer? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Always follow proper washing procedures. Please refer to the inside label for care instructions. It is recommended that all sweater knits be hand-washed in cold water or machine-washed on gentle cycle. Wash dark colors separately. Wash only with metal-free clothing if washing by machine. Use non-chlorine bleach if needed. Tumble dry on low and remove promptly. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        <b>Quick Tip:&nbsp;</b>To make garments last longer, close zippers completely and turn garment inside out. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Baseball Caps &nbsp;</b><br /><br />
                        <b>Can I wash the hats in a washing machine? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Hats should not be washed, you may find after washing them they lose their structure or shape. Should you need to clean a hat, spot cleaning is best option. Given the cost, your best option is to replace the hat. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Ties/Scarves &nbsp;</b><br /><br />
                        <b>Can I wash the ties in a washing machine? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Dry cleaning is recommended for longer lasting wear, however, if you have a stain, use mild soap and water to clean only the stain. Let the tie air dry. Do not submerge in water and do not bleach. A light iron is recommended. &nbsp;<br><br>
                        <b>Life expectancy &nbsp;</b><br>
                        We are often asked how long a uniform item should last. With continuous wear of uniform garments, the life expectancy of a uniform piece is approximately fifty washings. With proper care, most items will last longer. Harsh outdoor work conditions may cause some items to wear quicker. Also, if an item is washed and worn 3 –5 times per week you will notice wear and tear sooner. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        It’s important to have several uniform outfits so you can rotate your garments. Please replenish your uniform garments on a regular basis to maintain a fresh, crisp image. Please refer to your allotments under the GRBR Account to check your balance and utilize the uniform allowance Enterprise Holdings, Inc. provides. &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<br>
                        Please call or email IMAGE SOLUTIONS with uniform feedback and any quality concerns. We are continually looking to improve our uniform offerings and we welcome your feedback. <a href="mailto:cs@imageinc.com" rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank">cs@imageinc.com</a> or by phone M-F 11am-6pm EST (888)756-9898 &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        Are Enterprise Bus Drivers required to wear neckwear? &nbsp;<br>
                        Enterprise Bus Drivers are required to wear professional ties (male) or scarves (female). We now offer neckwear under the Enterprise brand Bus Driver category. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p> &nbsp;</p>&nbsp;
                    <h3 style="font-size:15px; "><u><b>Shipping </b></u></h3>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        At checkout, you will have the option to select FedEx Ground, FedEx 2nd Day Air, or FedEx Next Day Air.  The shipping charges for your orders will be billed with your final invoice. <br><br>
                        <b>How is sales tax calculated? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        Sales tax will be charged in accordance with your country’s tax rate. Taxes and duties will be calculated at time of checkout based on shipping address. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>How will I know that my order shipped? &nbsp;</b>
                    </p>
                    <p style="color:red;">
                        Customers receive an e-mail order acknowledgement as well as a shipping notification. &nbsp;
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Why wasn't my order shipped as soon as it was placed? &nbsp;</b><br>
                        In-stock merchandise is normally shipped out of our warehouse within 24 to 48 hours of placing your order (excluding holidays and weekends). If an item is showing “Stocking” or the order was placed over a weekend or holiday, the shipment could be delayed. &nbsp;
                    </p>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        <b>Calculating Shipping Time/Costs &nbsp;</b><br>
                        We use FedEx International to deliver orders outside the continental U.S. All orders are shipped from West Chester, OH. Shipping times are calculated from the time your order leaves our Image Solutions warehouse. In stock merchandise will ship out within 24 to 48 hours after order placement; excluding weekends and holidays. Shipping is delayed, of course, if an item is on backorder. Customers are responsible for tracking items once they have shipped. 
                    </p>
                    <h3 style="font-size:15px; "><u><b>Returns </b></u></h3>&nbsp;
                    <p>
                        All International orders are final.  Returns will not be accepted unless you receive a defective item.  If that happens, please contact Customer Service for resolution via email  M-F 8am – 8pm EST cs@imageinc.com or by phone M-F 11am-6pm EST (888)756-9898.
                    </p>
